docs.abstract: The international tax system is behind the times. But we need coordinated reform.
docs.snippet: The international tax system is behind the times. But we need coordinated reform.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last Thursday, the French Senate passed a digital services tax, which would impose an entirely new tax on large multinationals that provide digital services to consumers or users in France.

headline.main: Beware. Other Nations Will Follow France With Their Own Digital Tax.
headline.print_headline: Digital Services Will Be Taxed, but How?

docs.abstract: The attorney general, reopening the conversation on security vs. privacy, said that encryption and other measures effectively turned devices into “law-free zones.”
docs.snippet: The attorney general, reopening the conversation on security vs. privacy, said that encryption and other measures effectively turned devices into “law-free zones.”
docs.lead_paragraph: Attorney General William P. Barr said on Tuesday that technology companies should stop using advanced encryption and other security measures that effectively turn devices into “law-free zones” that keep out law enforcement officials conducting criminal investigations.

headline.main: Barr Revives Encryption Debate, Calling on Tech Firms to Allow for Law Enforcement
headline.print_headline: Barr Wants Tech Companies To Stop Blocking Out Police

docs.abstract: A new documentary offers an in-depth look at a company that envisioned technologies like iPhones, emojis and touch screens long before they arrived.
docs.snippet: A new documentary offers an in-depth look at a company that envisioned technologies like iPhones, emojis and touch screens long before they arrived.
docs.lead_paragraph: What happens when you invent a future that remains, resolutely, in the future? Sarah Kerruish and Matt Maude’s documentary “General Magic” looks at a Silicon Valley startup that in the early 1990s accurately imagined the world we’d be living in today. The developers, designers and engineers at General Magic worked on concepts like e-commerce, touch screens, animated emoticons and, most notably, a smartphone that would contain the world.

headline.main: ‘General Magic’ Review: A Startup Before Its Time

docs.abstract: The iPhone maker is adding patents and 2,200 Intel employees as it tries to reduce dependency on another chip maker, Qualcomm.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Apple said on Thursday that it would buy most of Intel’s smartphone-modem business for $1 billion, aiding its push to gain more control over faster wireless technology in iPhones.

headline.main: Apple Pays $1 Billion for Part of Intel’s Modem Business
headline.print_headline: Apple to Pay $1 Billion For Key Piece of Intel

docs.abstract: A series of hearings on Capitol Hill showed the rising force of the political backlash against the country’s tech giants.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Lawmakers leveled stinging criticism and sharp questions at Big Tech executives on Tuesday, attacking Amazon, Apple, Facebook and Google for their market power, their perceived bias as gatekeepers of communication and Facebook’s ambitions to reshape the financial industry.
